  "prompt": "How do I play gem TD in DOTA2 when there is no internet?",
  "response": "To play Gem TD (Tower Defense) in Dota 2 without an internet connection, you'll need to ensure that you have the game files and content downloaded and available for offline play. Here are the steps to set it up:\n\n1. **Download Dota 2 and the Gem TD Custom Game:**\n   - You'll need to have Dota 2 installed on your computer and ensure that you have downloaded the Gem TD custom game while you were connected to the internet.\n\n2. **Ensure Offline Availability:**\n   - Launch Dota 2 while connected to the internet to ensure all the custom game content is downloaded. Once you confirm that Gem TD is listed in your \"Play\" menu, you can then proceed to play offline.\n  \n3. **Go Offline:**\n   - You can go offline by going to the Steam client and selecting \"Go Offline\" from the Steam menu. \n\n4. **Launch Dota 2:**\n   - Open Dota 2 while in offline mode. You should still be able to access your downloaded custom games, including Gem TD.\n\n5. **Select Gem TD:**\n   - From the main menu, navigate to \"Play\" and choose \"Custom Games\". You should see Gem TD listed among the available custom games. Select it and start playing.\n\n6. **Follow Game Instructions:**\n   - Once in-game, follow the instructions within Gem TD to participate in the tower defense gameplay, where you will purchase towers, defend against waves of enemies, and manage resources.\n\n**Note:** Make sure to fully familiarize yourself with the mechanics of Gem TD and any specific strategies you want to employ, as the offline mode may have a different experience compared to playing online with other players.\n\nEnjoy your game!",
